# Docebo Embedded Learning SDK — HCP Portal Integration

## Architecture Context

Merz Aesthetics uses **Docebo** (merzaestheticsexchange.docebosaas.com) as the learning platform
but an **HCP Portal** (TYPO3-based) as the customer-facing frontend. Docebo content is delivered
to HCPs via the **Embedded Learning SDK** — either as **Building Blocks** (widgets injected into
portal HTML) or a **Launcher** (floating popup overlay). The portal backend (PHP/TYPO3) handles
JWT token generation; the frontend (vanilla JS) handles kernel init, widget rendering, and events.

## Platform Details

- **Docebo domain**: `https://merzaestheticsexchangesandbox.docebosaas.com`
- **API browser**: `https://merzaestheticsexchangesandbox.docebosaas.com/api-browser/`
- **Kernel URL**: Obtained via API call `GET /manage/v1/app/kernel` (returns latest SDK JS URL)
- **Embedded Learning admin**: Gear icon → Embedded learning → Manage

## Two Integration Patterns

### Pattern A: Building Blocks (Recommended for deep portal integration)

Widgets are injected directly into TYPO3 Fluid templates as HTML custom elements.
This gives full layout control and seamless UX within the portal.

### Pattern B: Launcher (Lightweight overlay)

A floating button/icon that opens a popup with Docebo widgets. Lower integration effort,
but the learning experience feels "bolted on" rather than native.

**Decision criteria**: If HCPs should consume training as a natural part of portal navigation
(e.g., product pages link to related courses), use Building Blocks. If training is a secondary
feature accessible from any page, use Launcher.

## Kernel Initialization (Both Patterns)

### Step 1: Load the kernel script

```html
<!-- In TYPO3 Fluid template or page header -->
<!-- kernel-link comes from GET /manage/v1/app/kernel API response -->
<script type="text/javascript" src="{kernel-link}"></script>
```

### Step 2: Token provider and kernel start

```javascript
/**
 * Docebo Embedded Learning — Kernel Initialization
 *
 * The token provider function is called by the SDK whenever it needs
 * a fresh access token (initial load + automatic refresh on expiry).
 * It MUST return a valid Docebo OAuth2 access_token string.
 *
 * CRITICAL: Never expose client_secret in frontend JS.
 * The TYPO3 backend endpoint handles JWT signing and token exchange.
 */
async function renewToken() {
  // Call your TYPO3 backend endpoint that generates a JWT and exchanges
  // it for a Docebo access_token server-side
  const response = await fetch('/api/docebo/token', {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
    credentials: 'same-origin' // send TYPO3 session cookie
  });

  if (!response.ok) {
    throw new Error('Docebo token renewal failed: ' + response.status);
  }

  const data = await response.json();
  return data.access_token; // Must return the token string, not the object
}

// Initialize the kernel
DSDK.kernel().setTokenProvider(renewToken);
DSDK.kernel().start({
  domain: 'https://merzaestheticsexchangesandbox.docebosaas.com',
  language: 'en' // or dynamically from portal user's language preference
});
```

### TYPO3 Backend Token Endpoint (PHP)

```php
<?php
// EXT:hcp_portal/Classes/Controller/DoceboTokenController.php

use Firebase\JWT\JWT;

class DoceboTokenController extends ActionController
{
    /**
     * Generate JWT and exchange for Docebo access_token.
     * Called by frontend renewToken() function.
     */
    public function getTokenAction(): ResponseInterface
    {
        // Get current HCP user from TYPO3 session
        $user = $this->getCurrentHcpUser();
        if (!$user) {
            return $this->jsonResponse(['error' => 'Not authenticated'], 401);
        }

        // Build JWT payload
        $now = time();
        $payload = [
            'iss' => $this->settings['docebo']['clientId'],
            'sub' => $user->getEmail(), // Must match Docebo username
            'aud' => 'merzaestheticsexchange.docebosaas.com',
            'iat' => $now,
            'exp' => $now + 3600
        ];

        // Sign with RS256 private key (stored securely, NOT in repo)
        $privateKey = file_get_contents($this->settings['docebo']['privateKeyPath']);
        $jwt = JWT::encode($payload, $privateKey, 'RS256');

        // Exchange JWT for Docebo access_token
        $ch = curl_init('https://merzaestheticsexchangesandbox.docebosaas.com/oauth2/token');
        curl_setopt_array($ch, [
            CURLOPT_POST => true,
            CURLOPT_RETURNTRANSFER => true,
            CURLOPT_POSTFIELDS => http_build_query([
                'grant_type' => 'urn:ietf:params:oauth:grant-type:jwt-bearer',
                'scope' => 'api',
                'assertion' => $jwt
            ])
        ]);

        $result = json_decode(curl_exec($ch), true);
        curl_close($ch);

        return $this->jsonResponse([
            'access_token' => $result['access_token'],
            'expires_in' => $result['expires_in']
        ]);
    }
}
```

## Building Blocks Widgets Reference

### Available Widgets

| Widget Tag | Purpose | Key Attributes |
|---|---|---|
| `<dcbo-course-player>` | Play course content with full tracking | `courseid`, `autoplay`, `sources`, `showfullscreen`, `showpip` |
| `<dcbo-my-courses-and-lp>` | List user's enrolled courses/LPs | `itemtype`, `itemstatus`, `includeplayer`, `hidecoursesinlp` |
| `<dcbo-course-list>` | Static or dynamic course catalog | `type` (static/dynamic), `coursesids`, `maxresults`, `includeplayer` |

### Course Player Widget

```html
<!-- Standalone course player for a specific course -->
<div class="hcp-learning-player">
  <dcbo-course-player
    id="hcpPlayer1"
    courseid="INSERT_COURSE_ID"
    autoplay="false"
    forcefullscreen="false"
    showfullscreen="true"
    showpip="true"
    showthumbsintoc="false"
    showpreview="true"
    showtoc="true">
  </dcbo-course-player>
</div>

<!-- Player linked to a course list (sources attribute) -->
<dcbo-course-player
  id="hcpPlayer2"
  autoplay="false"
  sources="hcpCourseList1">
</dcbo-course-player>
```

### My Courses and Learning Plans Widget

```html
<dcbo-my-courses-and-lp
  id="hcpMyCourses"
  includeplayer="true"
  itemtype="all"
  itemstatus="inprogress"
  hidecoursesinlp="false"
  autoplay="false"
  forcefullscreen="false"
  showthumbsintoc="false"
  showtoc="true"
  showpip="true"
  showfullscreen="true">
</dcbo-my-courses-and-lp>
```

### Course List Widget

```html
<!-- Static: show specific courses (e.g., for a product page) -->
<dcbo-course-list
  id="hcpCourseList1"
  type="static"
  widgettitle="Related Training"
  coursesids="181,189,190,191"
  includeplayer="false">
</dcbo-course-list>

<!-- Dynamic: global search-based catalog -->
<dcbo-course-list
  id="hcpCatalog"
  type="dynamic"
  widgettitle="Training Catalog"
  maxresults="20"
  includeplayer="false">
</dcbo-course-list>
```

### Linking Course List to External Player

```html
<!-- Course list WITHOUT built-in player -->
<dcbo-course-list
  id="courseListMain"
  type="dynamic"
  widgettitle="Available Courses"
  maxresults="20"
  includeplayer="false">
</dcbo-course-list>

<!-- Separate player that receives course selection from the list -->
<dcbo-course-player
  id="mainPlayer"
  autoplay="true"
  forcefullscreen="false"
  showfullscreen="true"
  showpip="true"
  sources="courseListMain">
</dcbo-course-player>
```

## JavaScript Commands & Events

### Controlling Widgets Programmatically

```javascript
// Navigate course player to a specific course
DSDK.widget('hcpPlayer1').command('load', { courseId: 123 });

// Refresh the My Courses widget
DSDK.widget('hcpMyCourses').command('refresh');

// Open course list dynamic search
DSDK.widget('hcpCatalog').command('search', { query: 'botox' });
```

### Event Listeners

```javascript
// Listen for course completion
DSDK.getEventManager().on('course.completed', (event, payload) => {
  console.log('Course completed:', payload);
  // payload includes: courseId, courseName, userId, completionDate
  // Trigger HCP Portal actions: update profile, show certificate link, etc.
  updateHcpCourseStatus(payload.courseId, 'completed');
});

// Listen for course started
DSDK.getEventManager().on('course.started', (event, payload) => {
  console.log('Course started:', payload);
  trackHcpLearningActivity(payload);
});

// Listen for training material completed
DSDK.getEventManager().on('trainingMaterial.completed', (event, payload) => {
  console.log('Training material completed:', payload);
});

// Listen for enrollment
DSDK.getEventManager().on('enrollment.created', (event, payload) => {
  console.log('User enrolled:', payload);
});

// Listen for widget ready (useful for loading states)
DSDK.getEventManager().on('widget.ready', (event, payload) => {
  // Hide loading spinner, show widget container
  document.getElementById(payload.widgetId + '-loader').style.display = 'none';
});
```

## CSS Customization

Building Blocks use CSS custom properties (tokens) for theming. Wrap them in the widget tag selector:

```css
/* Match HCP Portal brand colors */
dcbo-course-player {
  --dcb-flow-course-player-back-button-icon: 'close';
}

dcbo-my-courses-and-lp {
  --dcb-flow-primary-color: #00539B; /* Merz brand blue */
  --dcb-flow-font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif;
}

/* Container sizing within TYPO3 layout */
.hcp-learning-player {
  width: 100%;
  max-width: 960px;
  min-height: 540px;
  margin: 0 auto;
}
```

## Content Security Policy Requirements

If the HCP Portal uses CSP headers, add these directives:

```
script-src  'self' https://*.dcbstatic.com https://merzaestheticsexchangesandbox.docebosaas.com;
style-src   'self' https://*.dcbstatic.com 'unsafe-inline';
img-src     'self' https://*.dcbstatic.com https://merzaestheticsexchangesandbox.docebosaas.com;
frame-src   *.dcbstatic.net;
child-src   *.dcbstatic.net;
connect-src 'self' https://merzaestheticsexchangesandbox.docebosaas.com;
```

## Critical Rules

- **Never expose Docebo client_secret in frontend code** — all token exchange happens server-side in PHP
- **Always use `setTokenProvider()`** — never hardcode tokens; the SDK handles refresh cycles
- **Widget IDs must be unique per page** — the DSDK uses them for command routing and event targeting
- **SCORM/xAPI/AICC content may require third-party cookies** — the portal's cookie policy must allow this
- **The kernel URL changes with SDK updates** — always fetch it dynamically via `GET /manage/v1/app/kernel`
- **Course IDs are Docebo internal numeric IDs** — retrieve them from the API or platform URLs, never hardcode display names
- **Extended Enterprise users must be in the correct branch** before embedded content is visible — see `docebo-emea-branches.mdc`

## TYPO3 Integration Tips

- Load the kernel script via `page.includeJSFooterlibs` in TypoScript for proper load order
- Use Fluid ViewHelpers to inject course IDs dynamically based on the current product/page context
- Consider a TYPO3 content element (plugin) that renders a configurable Building Blocks widget
- Cache the kernel URL in TYPO3 caching framework (TTL ~24h) to avoid extra API calls per page load

